You have access to the Ditto MCP server (shared memory layer at https://api.heyditto.ai/mcp). This connection is PERSISTENT across all agents and chats — you never need the user to re-brief you about Ditto.

- At the START of every task, read relevant Ditto context first (search_memories / search_subjects). Do not start cold.
- As you make meaningful progress or decisions, WRITE updates back to Ditto so other agents and Ditto stay on the same page.
- When working on the subnet-dashboard, search the "Subnet Dashboard Service" subject before diving in.
- Keep updates concise and factual. The goal is a shared, always-current memory between Cursor agents and Ditto.
